@zerg-zerg this looks great :)

I just added some style nit comments. These aren't enforced by checkstyle but my aim is to be consistent with the rest of the codebase.

The builds are failing, but they don't seem to be related to these particular changes. Hopefully they'll fix themselves on a new push.

@shahankhatch Sorry for taking long. I was thinking when we use an existing evaluator we schedule a task based on locality. I.e., `SchedulerWithLocality.submitTask`  considers locality to choose which task to launch. In your implementation, you considered asking an evaluator based on the location of data. 

The PR fails the checks. Could you check if checkstyle and findbugs pass? 

@dafrista What would be better to implement?

@jsjason Thanks for review. I've addressed your comments.

To describe the change related to event handlers, this PR removes redundant wrapping of comm group event handlers.
Current implementation of `CommunicationGroupDriverImpl` adds topology handlers to `commGroup*Handler`, and `GroupCommDriverImpl` adds `commGroup*Handler` to `groupComm*Handler`. For `GroupCommMessageHandler`, we distinguish `commGroupMessageHandler` of different comm groups and hand over `GroupCommunicationMessage` to specific `commGroupMessageHandler`. On the other hand, we do not distinguish specific comm group (running task, failed task, failed evaluator) handlers from others,  handing over all events to all comm group handlers, and thus this wrapping is redundant.
